Berjaya Times Square.label: Berjaya Times Square
Berjaya Times Square.description: Berjaya Times Square Kuala Lumpur is a 48-storey, 203 m twin tower, hotel, condominium, indoor amusement park and shopping centre complex in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. Wikipedia

Bull Ring, Birmingham.label: Bull Ring, Birmingham
Bull Ring, Birmingham.description: The Bull Ring is a major commercial area of Birmingham. It has been an important feature of Birmingham since the Middle Ages, when its market was first held. Wikipedia

Galeries Lafayette.label: Galeries Lafayette
Galeries Lafayette.description: The Galeries Lafayette is an upmarket French department store company located on Boulevard Haussmann in the 9th arrondissement of Paris. In 2009, Galeries Lafayette recorded earnings of over one billion euro. Wikipedia

King of Prussia Mall.label: King of Prussia Mall
King of Prussia Mall.description: The King of Prussia Mall is the largest shopping mall in the United States of America in terms of leasable retail space. It is a luxury mall with numerous upscale retailers. Wikipedia

SM Megamall.label: SM Megamall
SM Megamall.description: SM Megamall is a shopping mall located in the Ortigas business district of Metro Manila, Philippines. Wikipedia

Suria KLCC.label: Suria KLCC
Suria KLCC.description: Suria KLCC is an end to end Developer and Asset Manager of Retail Assets in Malaysia. The largest retail asset, Suria KLCC, is detailed in this listing. Wikipedia

Toronto Eaton Centre.label: Toronto Eaton Centre
Toronto Eaton Centre.description: The Toronto Eaton Centre is a shopping mall and office complex in downtown Toronto, Ontario, Canada, named after the now-defunct Eaton's department store chain that once anchored it. Wikipedia

The Dubai Mall.label: The Dubai Mall
The Dubai Mall.description: The Dubai Mall is the world's largest shopping mall based on total area and thirteenth largest by gross leasable area. Located in Dubai, United Arab Emirates, it is part of the 20-billion-dollar Downtown Dubai complex, and includes 1,200 shops. Wikipedia

West Edmonton Mall.label: West Edmonton Mall
West Edmonton Mall.description: West Edmonton Mall, located in Edmonton, Alberta, Canada, is the largest shopping mall in North America and the tenth largest in the world by gross leasable area. The mall was founded by the Ghermezian brothers, who immigrated from Iran in 1959. Wikipedia

Drake Circus Shopping Centre.label: Drake Circus
Drake Circus Shopping Centre.description: Drake Circus Shopping Centre is a 425,000 square feet covered shopping mall in the centre of Plymouth, England which opened in October 2006. Wikipedia

Miller Hill Mall.label: Miller Hill Mall
Miller Hill Mall.description: Miller Hill Mall is a shopping mall located in Duluth, Minnesota, USA. It is located on U.S. Highway 53 where it intersects Trinity Road. Wikipedia

Pacific Place.label: Pacific Place
Pacific Place.description: Pacific Place is a complex of office towers, hotels and a shopping centre situated at 88 Queensway, in Admiralty, Hong Kong. The latest phase, Three Pacific Place, is located at 1 Queen's Road East. Wikipedia

Phipps Plaza.label: Phipps Plaza
Phipps Plaza.description: Phipps Plaza is an upscale shopping mall located in the affluent Buckhead district of Atlanta. Owned by Simon Property Group, the retail center is located at the intersection of Peachtree Road & Lenox ... Wikipedia

Pioneer Place.label: Pioneer Place
Pioneer Place.description: Pioneer Place is an upscale, urban shopping mall in downtown Portland, Oregon. It consists of four blocks of retail, dining, parking, and an office tower named Pioneer Tower. Wikipedia

The Landmark (Hong Kong).label: The Landmark
The Landmark (Hong Kong).description: The Landmark is an office and shopping development owned by Hongkong Land in Central, Hong Kong. It is commonly known as the home of numerous prestigious international brands and the gathering place of well-heeled shoppers. Wikipedia

Ušće Tower.label: Ušće Tower
Ušće Tower.description: Ušće Tower is a 25-story mixed use skyscraper located at 6 Mihajlo Pupin Boulevard in the Novi Beograd municipality of Belgrade, Serbia. Wikipedia

Valley River Center.label: Valley River Center
Valley River Center.description: Valley River Center is a super-regional-class shopping mall located in Eugene, Oregon, U.S. It is the largest shopping center between the Portland and San Francisco area with over 130 local and national stores and restaurants. Wikipedia

Concord Mall (Indiana).label: Concord Mall
Concord Mall (Indiana).description: Concord Mall is an enclosed shopping mall serving Elkhart, Indiana. It opened in 1972 and is anchored by J. C. Penney, Carson's, and Hobby Lobby. Wikipedia

American Dream Meadowlands.label: Meadowlands Xanadu
American Dream Meadowlands.description: American Dream Meadowlands is a stalled retail and entertainment complex located in the Meadowlands Sports Complex in East Rutherford, New Jersey. It was first proposed in 2003 by the Mills Corporation as the Meadowlands Xanadu. Wikipedia
American Dream Meadowlands.type: Shopping mall in East Rutherford, New Jersey

Brea Mall.label: Brea Mall
Brea Mall.description: The Brea Mall is a shopping mall located in the Orange County city of Brea, California. Since 1998 the mall has been owned and operated by the Simon Property Group. Wikipedia

Bronx Terminal Market.label: Bronx Terminal Market
Bronx Terminal Market.description: Bronx Terminal Market, formerly known as Gateway Center at Bronx Terminal Market is a shopping center at Exterior Street in The Bronx, New York. Wikipedia

Buchanan Galleries.label: Buchanan Galleries
Buchanan Galleries.description: Buchanan Galleries is a shopping centre located in the central area of Glasgow, the largest city in Scotland. Construction began in 1996 and the building opened to the public on 31 March 1999. Wikipedia

Broadway at the Beach.label: Broadway at the Beach
Broadway at the Beach.description: Broadway at the Beach is a shopping center located in Myrtle Beach, South Carolina. Since its inception in 1996, it has grown to be one of Myrtle Beach's premier shopping destinations. Wikipedia

Centerpoint Mall (Toronto).label: Centerpoint Mall
Centerpoint Mall (Toronto).description:
Centerpoint Mall is a shopping mall located in Toronto, Ontario, Canada on the corner of Steeles Avenue and Yonge Street.
It is home to Canadian Tire, Target, The Bay, Shoppers Drug Mart, and a No Frills. Wikipedia

Bay Park Square.label: Bay Park Square
Bay Park Square.description: Bay Park Square is a shopping mall owned by Simon Property Group, in the Green Bay, Wisconsin suburb of Ashwaubenon, in the United States. The mall opened in 1980 under the ownership of DeBartolo Corporation. Wikipedia

Causeway Point.label: Causeway Point
Causeway Point.description: Causeway Point, is the seventh largest suburban shopping mall in Singapore, located in the town centre of Woodlands, a town in the north of Singapore. Wikipedia

Centerpointe Mall.label: Centerpointe Mall
Centerpointe Mall.description: Centerpointe Mall was an enclosed shopping mall located in Grand Rapids, Michigan, United States. It opened in 1967 as Eastbrook Mall, a year before the larger Woodland Mall opened across the street. Demolition of portions of the mall began in 2012. Wikipedia

Central City Shopping Centre.label: Central City Shopping Centre
Central City Shopping Centre.description: Central City Shopping Centre is a shopping mall and office tower complex in Whalley, Surrey, British Columbia, Canada, which is owned by Blackwood Partners Management Corporation. Wikipedia

Churchill Square (Brighton and Hove).label: Churchill Square
Churchill Square (Brighton and Hove).description:
Churchill Square is the major city-centre shopping centre, NCP and central bus station in the city of Brighton and Hove, United Kingdom.
It was originally built during the 1960s, obscuring several streets. Wikipedia

CityPlace.label: CityPlace (West Palm Beach)
CityPlace.description: CityPlace (West Palm Beach) is an upscale lifestyle center in downtown West Palm Beach, Florida along South Rosemary Avenue. Besides shops and restaurants, the center also includes rental apartments, condos, and offices. Wikipedia

City Creek Center.label: City Creek Center
City Creek Center.description: The City Creek Center is a mixed-use development with an upscale open-air shopping center, office and residential buildings, fountain, and simulated creek near Temple Square in downtown Salt Lake City, Utah. Wikipedia

Citypark Albania.label: Citypark Albania
Citypark Albania.description: Citypark Albania is a shopping mall in Albania. located along the Durrës – Tirana highway. Wikipedia

Copley Place.label: Copley Place
Copley Place.description: Copley Place is an upscale shopping mall in the Back Bay section of Boston, Massachusetts, as part of a larger complex that includes office buildings, two hotels, and a parking garage. Wikipedia

Cordova Mall.label: Cordova Mall
Cordova Mall.description: Cordova Mall, located in Pensacola, Florida, is the largest shopping center on the northwest Gulf Coast of Florida. It is currently owned and managed by Simon Property Group, who acquired it in 1998. Wikipedia

Dixie Square Mall.label: Dixie Square Mall
Dixie Square Mall.description: Dixie Square Mall was an enclosed shopping mall located in Harvey, Illinois, United States, at the junction of 151st Street and the Dixie Highway. It stood vacant for over 30 years, more than twice as long as it was in business. Wikipedia

Fox River Mall.label: Fox River Mall
Fox River Mall.description: Fox River Mall is a mall located at 4301 W Wisconsin Ave., Appleton, Wisconsin in the United States. This mall opened on July 18, 1984. Wikipedia

Eden, High Wycombe.label: Eden, High Wycombe
Eden, High Wycombe.description: Eden is a shopping and entertainment complex in High Wycombe, Buckinghamshire in the south east of England. Wikipedia

Galleria Edina.label: Galleria Edina
Galleria Edina.description: The Galleria is an upscale shopping mall in Edina, Minnesota anchored solely by Gabberts Furniture. This mall is located directly across the street from the world's first enclosed mall, Southdale Center, which originally opened in 1956. Wikipedia

Glenbrook Square.label: Glenbrook Square
Glenbrook Square.description: Glenbrook Square is located at 4201 Coldwater Road, in Fort Wayne, Indiana. Built in 1966 by Chicago-based Landau & Heyman and originally known as Glenbrook Center, Glenbrook Square has been owned and ... Wikipedia

Greenacres Shopping Centre.label: Greenacres Shopping Centre
Greenacres Shopping Centre.description: Greenacres Shopping Centre is a shopping mall in Port Elizabeth, South Africa. It was opened on 22 October 1981, and is Port Elizabeth's largest shopping mall. It attracts more than a million shoppers a month. Wikipedia

Guam Premier Outlets.label: Guam Premier Outlets
Guam Premier Outlets.description: Guam Premier Outlets or GPO is a shopping mall located in Tamuning, Guam. GPO is the only outlet mall in the United States territory of Guam. Wikipedia

Hanes Mall.label: Hanes Mall
Hanes Mall.description: Hanes Mall is a shopping mall located off I-40 on Silas Creek Parkway between Stratford Road and Hanes Mall Boulevard in Winston-Salem, North Carolina. The mall has 1,558,860 square feet GLA and has 5 anchor stores and over 200 tenants in all. Wikipedia

International Plaza and Bay Street.label: International Plaza and Bay Street
International Plaza and Bay Street.description: International Plaza and Bay Street is a large upscale shopping mall located in the Westshore business district of Tampa, Florida. Wikipedia

Itis shopping centre.label: Itis shopping centre
Itis shopping centre.description: Itis is a shopping centre in the district of Itäkeskus in East Helsinki, Finland. It is the largest fully enclosed shopping centre in the Nordic countries, with a gross leasable area of 120,300 square ... Wikipedia

Jordan Creek Town Center.label: Jordan Creek Town Center
Jordan Creek Town Center.description: Jordan Creek Town Center is a super-regional shopping mall and lifestyle center in the American city of West Des Moines, Iowa. It is the largest shopping complex in the state of Iowa with a total gross leasable area of 1,340,000 square feet. Wikipedia

Kamppi Center.label: Kamppi Center
Kamppi Center.description: Kamppi Centre is a complex in the Kamppi district in the centre of Helsinki, designed by various architects, the main designer, however, being Juhani Pallasmaa. It is said to be Helsinki's new downtown commercial and residential centre. Wikipedia

Katy Mills.label: Katy Mills
Katy Mills.description: Katy Mills is an outlet shopping mall in Katy, Texas within the Houston–Sugar Land–Baytown metropolitan area, developed by The Mills Corporation and now owned by Simon Property Group. Wikipedia

Kowloon City Plaza.label: Kowloon City Plaza
Kowloon City Plaza.description: Kowloon City Plaza is one of the shopping malls located at Kowloon City in Hong Kong. It was established in December 1993. Wikipedia

Lafayette Square Mall.label: Lafayette Square Mall
Lafayette Square Mall.description: Lafayette Square Mall is a super-regional shopping mall in Indianapolis, Indiana. Developed in 1968 by Edward J. DeBartolo Sr., the mall is managed by Jones Lang LaSalle and owned by Ashkenazy Acquisition Corp. Wikipedia

Lakeside Joondalup Shopping City.label: Lakeside Joondalup Shopping City
Lakeside Joondalup Shopping City.description: Lakeside Joondalup Shopping City is a major shopping centre, located in Joondalup, a northern suburb of Perth. It is located next to Grand Boulevard, approximately 100 metres from Joondalup railway station. Wikipedia

Mayfair Mall.label: Mayfair Mall
Mayfair Mall.description: Mayfair Mall is a shopping mall located on Mayfair Road between North Avenue and Center Street in Wauwatosa, Wisconsin, USA. Mayfair Shopping Center was constructed in 1958 by the Hunzinger Construction Company. Wikipedia

Merry Hill Shopping Centre.label: Merry Hill Shopping Centre
Merry Hill Shopping Centre.description: Merry Hill is a shopping centre in Brierley Hill near Dudley, West Midlands, England. It was developed between 1985 and 1990, with several expansion and renovation projects taking place since. Wikipedia

Mic Mac Mall.label: Mic Mac Mall
Mic Mac Mall.description: Mic Mac Mall is a Canadian shopping mall located in Nova Scotia's Halifax Regional Municipality, in the city of Dartmouth. It is owned by Ivanhoe Cambridge headquartered in Montreal, Quebec. Wikipedia

Miracle Mile Shops.label: Miracle Mile Shops
Miracle Mile Shops.description: Miracle Mile Shops is a 475,000 square foot, 1.2-mile long, enclosed shopping mall on the Las Vegas Strip in Las Vegas, Nevada. It is home to more than 170 stores, 15 restaurants and live entertainment venues. Wikipedia

Myyrmanni.label: Myyrmanni
Myyrmanni.description: Myyrmanni is a shopping center located at the Myyrmäki suburb of Vantaa, Finland. The center was built in the early 1990s and it has over 120 stores and 1,100 parking spaces. It was the site of the Myyrmanni bombing on October 11, 2002. Wikipedia

NorthPark Mall (Iowa).label: NorthPark Mall
NorthPark Mall (Iowa).description: NorthPark Mall is a shopping mall located in Davenport, Iowa. As Davenport is part of the Quad Cities of Illinois and Iowa the mall serves the population of these cities. Wikipedia

North Star Mall.label: North Star Mall
North Star Mall.description: North Star Mall is a shopping mall in San Antonio, Texas, USA with anchor tenants Dillard's, J.C. Penney, Macy's, Saks Fifth Avenue, and Forever 21. Wikipedia

Northgate Shopping Centre.label: Northgate Shopping Centre, Johannesburg
Northgate Shopping Centre.description: Northgate Shopping Centre is a shopping centre in Johannesburg, South Africa. It is located in Northriding. It has one of the few remaining functioning ice-rinks in the area. Wikipedia

Northpark Mall (Missouri).label: Northpark Mall
Northpark Mall (Missouri).description: Northpark Mall is a regional mall located in Joplin, Missouri. The mall opened in 1972. It features more than 100 inline tenants, including a food court and four anchor stores, as well as TJ Maxx and Vintage Stock. Wikipedia

Oakbrook Center.label: Oakbrook Center
Oakbrook Center.description: Oakbrook Center is an upscale super-regional shopping center located near Interstate 88 in Oak Brook, Illinois. It was originally opened in 1962. Wikipedia

Oberon Mall.label: Oberon Mall
Oberon Mall.description: Oberon Mall is a shopping mall located in the Indian city of Kochi and the current second largest lifestyle mall in Kerala in operation, after the newer and bigger Lulu Cochin Mall. Wikipedia

Oglethorpe Mall.label: Oglethorpe Mall
Oglethorpe Mall.description: Oglethorpe Mall is a super-regional shopping mall on the Southside of Savannah, Georgia. Wikipedia

Ontario Mills.label: Ontario Mills
Ontario Mills.description: Ontario Mills is a large enclosed shopping mall, marketed as an outlet mall. It is located in Ontario, California and it is one of the primary tourist attractions in the Inland Empire. Wikipedia

Opry Mills.label: Opry Mills
Opry Mills.description: Opry Mills is a super-regional shopping mall owned by Simon Property Group, formerly by its initial owners Mills Corporation and Gaylord Entertainment. It opened in Nashville, Tennessee in 2000 on the former site of the Opryland USA theme park. Wikipedia

Galleria at Crystal Run.label: Galleria at Crystal Run
Galleria at Crystal Run.description: The Galleria at Crystal Run is a shopping mall in Wallkill, New York and is the second largest mall in New York's Hudson Valley region. Wikipedia

Palisades Center.label: Palisades Center
Palisades Center.description: The Palisades Center Mall, often referred to as the Palisades Mall, in West Nyack, New York is the eighth largest shopping mall in the United States by total area, and sixth largest by gross leasable space. Wikipedia

Pearlridge.label: Pearlridge
Pearlridge.description: Pearlridge is the second largest shopping center in Hawaiʻi, after Ala Moana, and is Hawaiʻi's largest enclosed shopping center, located in ʻAiea. Wikipedia

Polo Park.label: Polo Park
Polo Park.description: Polo Park is Winnipeg's largest retail and entertainment district. It is the largest mall out of the eight malls in the city. Situated on the former Polo Park Racetrack, the Polo Park Mall was built in 1959. Wikipedia

Pittsburgh Mills.label: Pittsburgh Mills
Pittsburgh Mills.description: The Pittsburgh Mills is a super-regional shopping mall complex northeast of Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania in Frazer Township, along PA Route 28 near its intersection with the Pennsylvania Turnpike. Wikipedia

Riverchase Galleria.label: Riverchase Galleria
Riverchase Galleria.description: Riverchase Galleria, locally known as The Galleria, is a large upscale, super–regional shopping mall in the Birmingham suburb of Hoover, Alabama. It is the 43rd largest shopping mall in the United States. Wikipedia

Roosevelt Field (shopping mall).label: Roosevelt Field
Roosevelt Field (shopping mall).description: Roosevelt Field is an American shopping mall. It is the second-largest full price shopping mall in the state of New York and tenth in the country as measured by gross leaseable area at 2,244,581 ft². It is owned and managed by Simon Property Group. Wikipedia

Siam Center.label: Siam Center
Siam Center.description: Siam Center is a shopping center in Bangkok, Thailand. It was opened in 1973 and includes a wide range of concept shops. Wikipedia

Sim Lim Square.label: Sim Lim Square
Sim Lim Square.description: Sim Lim Square, commonly referred to as SLS, is a large retail complex that offers a wide variety of electronic goods and services ranging from DVDs, cameras, phones, video cameras, and computer parts and servicing. Wikipedia

SouthGate, Bath.label: SouthGate, Bath
SouthGate, Bath.description: SouthGate is a shopping centre in Bath, Somerset, England. It replaced a shopping centre which was demolished in 2007. Wikipedia

SouthPark Mall (Moline, Illinois).label: SouthPark Mall
SouthPark Mall (Moline, Illinois).description: SouthPark Mall is the name of the shopping mall located in Moline, Illinois. As Moline is part of the Quad Cities of Illinois and Iowa, the mall serves the population of these cities. Wikipedia

South Coast Plaza.label: South Coast Plaza
South Coast Plaza.description: South Coast Plaza is an upscale-luxury shopping center in Costa Mesa, California, USA, in Orange County. The largest mall on the west coast, its sales of over 1.5 billion are highest in the United States. Wikipedia

Stanford Shopping Center.label: Stanford Shopping Center
Stanford Shopping Center.description: Stanford Shopping Center is an upscale open air shopping mall located on Route 82 at Sand Hill Road in Palo Alto, California. Wikipedia

Tampines 1.label: Tampines 1
Tampines 1.description: Tampines 1 is a shopping mall in the east of Singapore located beside the Tampines. The mall opened on 9 April 2009. It replaced the former DBS Tampines Centre and Pavilion Cineplex. Wikipedia

The Core Shopping Centre (Calgary).label: The CORE Shopping Centre
The Core Shopping Centre (Calgary).description: The Core Shopping Centre, which consists of TD Square, the Holt Renfrew building, and the former Calgary Eaton Centre, is the dominant shopping complex located in the downtown core of Calgary, Alberta, Canada. Wikipedia

The Domain (Austin, Texas).label: The Domain
The Domain (Austin, Texas).description: The Domain is a high-density business, retail, and residential center operated by Simon Property Group and Endeavor Real Estate Group, and is located in the high-tech corridor of northwest Austin, Texas. Wikipedia

The Florida Mall.label: The Florida Mall
The Florida Mall.description: The Florida Mall is an upscale shopping mall located in unincorporated Orlando, Florida, on the southeast corner of Orange Blossom Trail and Sand Lake Road; it opened in 1986. Wikipedia

The Fort Shopping Park.label: The Fort Shopping Park
The Fort Shopping Park.description: The Fort Shopping Park is a shopping centre in Castle Bromwich near Birmingham, West Midlands, England. It was built on part of the former tyre factory of Dunlop Rubber. Wikipedia

The Forum Shops at Caesars.label: The Forum Shops at Caesars
The Forum Shops at Caesars.description: The Forum Shops at Caesars is a 636,000-square-foot shopping mall connected to Caesars Palace on the Las Vegas Strip in Las Vegas, Nevada. Wikipedia

The Gallery at Market East.label: The Gallery at Market East
The Gallery at Market East.description: The Gallery at Market East, or "The Gallery" as it is known to locals, is an urban mall in downtown Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, United States with over 130 stores and a food court. Wikipedia

The Johnstown Galleria.label: The Johnstown Galleria
The Johnstown Galleria.description: The Johnstown Galleria is a two-level, enclosed super-regional shopping mall in Richland Township, Cambria County, Pennsylvania, southeast of the city of Johnstown. Wikipedia

Trafford Centre.label: Trafford Centre
Trafford Centre.description: The Trafford Centre is a large indoor shopping centre and leisure complex in Dumplington, Greater Manchester, England. Wikipedia

Valley View Mall (Roanoke, Virginia).label: Valley View Mall
Valley View Mall (Roanoke, Virginia).description: Valley View Mall is a 800,000-square-foot regional shopping mall located in the Roundhill neighborhood of Roanoke, Virginia. Wikipedia

Westfield Galleria at Roseville.label: Westfield Galleria at Roseville
Westfield Galleria at Roseville.description: Westfield Galleria at Roseville is an upscale shopping mall in Roseville, California, United States. Wikipedia

Westfield Garden City.label: Westfield Garden City
Westfield Garden City.description: Westfield Garden City, better known as Garden City, is one of Brisbane's major shopping centres, located in the suburb of Upper Mount Gravatt. The centre is operated by Westfield, and previously operated by AMP Limited before the takeover in 2003. Wikipedia

Southgate Centre.label: Southgate Centre
Southgate Centre.description: Southgate Centre is a shopping centre located in south Edmonton, Alberta, Canada, covering just under 1 million square feet. Wikipedia

Four Seasons Town Centre.label: Four Seasons Town Centre
Four Seasons Town Centre.description: Four Seasons Town Centre is a three-story shopping mall in Greensboro, North Carolina. Opened in 1974, it was the first enclosed shopping center in Greensboro. Wikipedia
